# Quick Start

## Launch Claude Workspace

### Windows Desktop
- **Double-click**: `Claude-Workspace.bat` on Desktop

### WSL Terminal
```bash
cw                    # Short alias
claude-workspace      # Full alias
cwdir                 # Just navigate to directory
```

### Manual
```bash
cd /mnt/c/Users/Password/Documents/ClaudeCodeProjects
claude
```

---

## First Commands

### Start a Session
```
Use the project-manager agent to initialize today's session
```

### Check Available Agents
```
Use the agent-router to help me choose an agent
```

### Maintain Context (every 15-20 interactions)
```
Use the context-keeper agent to refresh session state
```

### End Session
```
Use the project-manager agent to generate today's daily report
```

---

## MCP Tools Available

After restart, these tools are available:

### SQLite Database
```
Create a table to track my tasks
Query all tasks from the database
```

### Filesystem
```
List all files in the knowledge directory
Read the contents of project-status.md
```

### Memory (Knowledge Graph)
```
Remember that the API endpoint is /v1/users
What do you remember about the API?
```

---

## Key Directories

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.claude/agents/` | Subagent definitions |
| `projects/` | Your project workspaces |
| `knowledge/` | Persistent knowledge base |
| `reports/` | Daily/weekly reports |
| `data/` | Database and cached data |

---

## Emergency Commands

### Refresh context if feeling lost
```
Use the context-keeper agent to refresh session state
```

### Check what's been done
```
Use the project-manager agent to show current status
```

### Find the right agent
```
Use the agent-router for [describe your task]
```
